               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Maṣḥafa gәbrä ḥǝmāmāt “Book of the Rite of the Holy Week” (fols.
                     3ra-205rb)&#xD; I-1) Introduction (fols. 3ra-6ra)&#xD; I-2) Eve of Palm Sunday
                     (fols. 6ra-9rb)&#xD; I-3) Palm Sunday (fols. 9rb-11vc, 16ra-21vc, 26ra-vb)&#xD;
                     I-4) Monday (fols. 26vb-50vb)&#xD; - Night hours (fols. 26vb-30rb)&#xD; - Day
                     hours (fols. 30rb-50vb), including: Homily by John Chrysostom for Monday
                     morning (fols. 35vb-37ra); Homily by John Chrysostom on the fig tree for Monday
                     morning (fols. 37ra-41vb)&#xD; I-5) Tuesday (fols. 50vb-74rb)&#xD; - Night
                     hours (fols. 50vb-54rb)&#xD; - Day hours (fols. 54rb-74rb)&#xD; I-6) Wednesday
                     (fols. 74rb-93rc)&#xD; - Night hours (fols. 74rb-77va)&#xD; - Day hours (fols.
                     77va-93rc)&#xD; I-7) Thursday (fols. 93rc-116vc, 12ra-15rc), fols. misplaced
                     [inserted in Text I-3]&#xD; - Night hours (fols. 93rc-97ra)&#xD; - Day hours
                     (fols. 97ra-116vc, 12ra-15rc)&#xD; I-8) Friday (fols. 15rc-vc, 22ra-25vc,
                     117ra-191ra), fols. misplaced [inserted in Text I-3]&#xD; - Night hours (fols.
                     15rc-vc, 22ra-25vc, 117ra-131rc), including: Homily by John [Chrysostom] on
                     Christ when He says “If it be possible, let this chalice pass” (fols.
                     118vc-123rc); Tǝmhǝrta ḫǝbuʾāt “Teaching of Mysteries” (fols. 127va-129rc)&#xD;
                     - Day hours (fols. 132ra-191ra), including: Homily by Jaqob of Serug on Abraham
                     (fols. 153vc-162va)&#xD; I-9) Saturday (fols. 191ra-205rb)&#xD; - Night hours
                     (fols. 191ra-195rb)&#xD; - Mass (fols. 195rb-200vb)&#xD; - Evening (fols.
                     200vb-205rb)&#xD; &#xD; Additio 1; colophon.</summary>
